title: M20 coastbound still closed after crash
text:
Motorists are advised that the coastbound carriageway of the M20 between junctions 8 and 9 is currently closed following a collision in which a pedestrian died.
Kent Police were called at 6.47am on Wednesday 14 October and officers from the Serious Collision Investigation Unit are at the scene.
The carriageway is likely to be closed for several hours.
Anyone who may have witnessed this collision is asked to call the Serious Collision Investigation Unit's witness appeal line on 01622 798538.
Last updated Wed 14 Oct 2015 Travel
